ollect 6 points and buy something from the basic ability selection, e.g. runspeed(running faster). After 6 points of AA you will be able to select arch skills<br>- Collect another 12 points and spend them from the arch skill menu. E.g. put the 12 points into natural durability to increase your HPs by maybe 200.<br>- Collect another 5 points and you will be able to buy holy steed from the class selection menu. You then can create a hotkey when pressed will summon a holy steed.<br><br>So if you grind 4 hours straight each day you will take 23 to 46 days to get your holy steed.<br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utasan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tasan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 4:48:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=87.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: holy steed?</span><hr size=1> Build up 23 points in your Alternate Advancement experience bar and<br><br>Spend 6 AA points on any General Abilities of your choice,<br>Spend 12 AA points on any Archetype Abilities of your choice,<br>Spend 5 points on the Holy Steed ability in our class choices<br><br>Create a hotkey for this ability from the same menu and use it!<br><br>Sir Tasan<br>Innit<br>Antonius Bayle<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umagmel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magmel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font 